## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="ee837-154">O <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider.BuildSiteMap%2A> método é chamado para carregar e compilar o mapa do site do armazenamento persistente.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ee837-154">The <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider.BuildSiteMap%2A> method is called to load and build the site map from persistent storage.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="ee837-155">Para o comportamento padrão quando a filtragem de segurança é habilitada, consulte "Comentários" em <xref:System.Web.SiteMapProvider.IsAccessibleToUser%2A>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ee837-155">For the default behavior when security trimming is enabled, see "Remarks" in <xref:System.Web.SiteMapProvider.IsAccessibleToUser%2A>.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="ee837-156">Após o <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider> objeto analisa e carrega os dados de mapa de site, todos carregados <xref:System.Web.SiteMapNode> objetos e <xref:System.Web.SiteMapNodeCollection> coleções são somente leitura.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ee837-156">After the <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider> object parses and loads site map data, all loaded <xref:System.Web.SiteMapNode> objects and <xref:System.Web.SiteMapNodeCollection> collections are made read-only.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="ee837-157">Quando o <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider> analisa o <xref:System.Web.SiteMapNode.Url%2A> propriedade de um arquivo de mapa de site, ele converte URLs relativo do aplicativo, bem como as URLs relativas, para os caminhos virtuais absoluto do aplicativo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ee837-157">When the <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider> parses the <xref:System.Web.SiteMapNode.Url%2A> property from a site map file, it converts application-relative URLs, as well as relative URLs, to application-absolute virtual paths.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="ee837-158">O <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider> se inscreve para notificações de alteração de arquivo para o arquivo. sitemap.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ee837-158">The <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider> subscribes to file change notifications for the .sitemap file.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="ee837-159">Se qualquer alteração for feita para o arquivo. sitemap, o <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider> é recarregado, e a estrutura do mapa de site seja reconstruída.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ee837-159">If any change is made to the .sitemap file, the <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider> is reloaded, and the site map structure is rebuilt.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="ee837-160">O exemplo de código a seguir demonstra como criar uma nova instância do <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider> de classe e inicializá-lo para criar um mapa de site a partir de dados XML.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ee837-160">The following code example demonstrates how to create a new instance of the <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider> class and initialize it to build a site map from XML data.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
<%@ Page Language="c#" %>  
 <!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0 Transitional//EN">  
 <SCRIPT runat="server">  
 private void Page_Load(object sender, System.EventArgs e)  
 {  
     // Create an instance of the XmlSiteMapProvider class.  
     XmlSiteMapProvider testXmlProvider = new XmlSiteMapProvider();  
     NameValueCollection providerAttributes = new NameValueCollection(1);  
     providerAttributes.Add("siteMapFile","test.sitemap");  
     // Initialize the provider with a provider name and file name.  
     testXmlProvider.Initialize("testProvider", providerAttributes);  
  
     // The BuildSiteMap method is implicitly called when the   
     // RootNode propety is accessed.  
  
     // Prints "/myvirtualdirectory/WebForm1.aspx"  
     Response.Write(testXmlProvider.RootNode.Url + "<BR>");  
     // Prints "/myvirtualdirectory/WebForm2.aspx"  
     Response.Write(testXmlProvider.CurrentNode.Url + "<BR>");  
 }  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="ee837-161">O exemplo de código anterior usa um arquivo XML que está localizado na raiz virtual do aplicativo ASP.NET.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ee837-161">The preceding code example uses an XML file that is located in the virtual root of the ASP.NET application.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="ee837-162">O arquivo tem o seguinte formato:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ee837-162">The file has the following format:</span></span>  
  
```  
<siteMap>  
     <siteMapNode title="RootNode" description="The root page." url="WebForm1.aspx">  
         <siteMapNode title="CurrentNode" description="Some sub page." url="WebForm2.aspx"/>  
     </siteMapNode>  
 </siteMap>  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="ee837-250">O <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider> classe substitui o herdadas <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider.Initialize%2A> método para aplicar vários atributos, como o `siteMapFile` e `description` atributos, como o `attributes` coleção.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ee837-250">The <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider> class overrides the inherited <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider.Initialize%2A> method to apply several attributes, such as the `siteMapFile` and `description` attributes, to the `attributes` collection.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="ee837-251">O exemplo de código a seguir demonstra como criar uma nova instância do <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider> de classe e inicializá-lo para criar um mapa de site a partir de dados XML.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ee837-251">The following code example demonstrates how to create a new instance of the <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider> class and initialize it to build a site map from XML data.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
<%@ Page Language="c#" %>  
<SCRIPT runat="server">  
 private void Page_Load(object sender, System.EventArgs e) {  
     // Create an instance of the XmlSiteMapProvider class.  
     XmlSiteMapProvider testXmlProvider = new XmlSiteMapProvider();  
     NameValueCollection providerAttributes = new NameValueCollection(1);  
     providerAttributes.Add("siteMapFile","test.sitemap");  
  
     // Initialize the provider with a provider name and file name.  
     testXmlProvider.Initialize("testProvider", providerAttributes);  
  
     // Call the BuildSiteMap to load the site map information into memory.  
     testXmlProvider.BuildSiteMap();  
  
     // Prints "/myvirtualdirectory/WebForm1.aspx"  
     Response.Write(testXmlProvider.RootNode.Url + "<BR>");  
  
     // Prints "/myvirtualdirectory/WebForm2.aspx"  
     Response.Write(testXmlProvider.CurrentNode.Url + "<BR>");  
 }  
 </SCRIPT>  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="ee837-252">O exemplo de código anterior usa um arquivo XML que está localizado na raiz virtual do aplicativo ASP.NET.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ee837-252">The preceding code example uses an XML file that is located in the virtual root of the ASP.NET application.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="ee837-253">O arquivo tem o seguinte formato:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ee837-253">The file has the following format:</span></span>  
  
```  
<siteMap>  
  <siteMapNode title="RootNode" description="The root page." url="WebForm1.aspx">  
    <siteMapNode title="CurrentNode" description="Some sub page." url="WebForm2.aspx"/>  
  </siteMapNode>  
</siteMap>  
```
